  "texts": [
    "Given a partial-state frameF = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ and ⊥ ̸ ∈ S, define F ⊥ = ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥, ⊥, {R i ⊥ } i∈I, P ⊥ ⟩ as follows: S ⊥ = S ∪ {⊥}; x ⊑ ⊥ y iff x ⊑ y or x = ⊥; xR i ⊥ y iff xR i y or y = ⊥; and P ⊥ = {X ∪ {⊥} | X ∈ P }.Given a valuation π: Φ → P, define π ⊥: Φ → P ⊥ by π ⊥ (p) = π(p) ∪ {⊥}.",
    "◁The following fact records that restriction and extension work as desired.Fact 4.24 (Equivalence of Extended and Restricted Frames).",
    "For any possibility frame F and extended possibility frame E:1.",
    "F ⊥ is an extended possibility frame such that (F ⊥) -= F, and for any possibility model ⟨F, π⟩, x ∈ F, andφ ∈ L(Φ, I), ⟨F, π⟩, x ⊩ φ iff ⟨F ⊥, π ⊥ ⟩, x ⊩ φ;2.",
